# Task Completion Summary

**Task:** B05_trainer-entry-home-and-weakness-summary
**Completed At:** 2026-04-03
**Mode:** Code

## Results

Implemented both user-visible trainer surfaces mounted through the shared trainer shell:

1. **Trainer Entry Home** (`src/js/trainer/trainer-entry-home.js`)
   - Navigation bar with csTimer Trainer branding and tab navigation (Train/Stats/Timer)
   - Hero section with "What do you want to practice today?" prompt
   - Three goal selection cards: Return to Speed, Last Layer, Cross
   - CTA button to begin training session (navigates to setup surface)
   - Quick stats section showing sessions, cases drilled, PLL/OLL confidence
   - Recent sessions grid with progress bars
   - Loads real data from trainerIntegration (sessions, stats)
   - Falls back gracefully when no data exists

2. **Weakness Summary** (`src/js/trainer/weakness-summary.js`)
   - Page header with category tabs (PLL/OLL/Cross/All)
   - Stats overview row (total sessions, cases trained, avg recognition, confidence, weak cases)
   - Confidence panels for PLL and OLL with Mastered/Learning/Weak/Untrained breakdowns
   - Case rankings table sorted by slowest first with confidence bars, trend indicators, and per-case Drill buttons
   - 30-day trend sparklines for recognition time, confidence score, and weak case count
   - Tab switching refreshes ranking table for selected category
   - Loads real data from trainerIntegration (sessions, stats, catalog)

3. **Trainer Init** (`src/js/trainer/trainer-init.js`)
   - Wires both surfaces into the trainer shell via registerMount
   - Exposes showEntry() and showWeaknessSummary() convenience functions
   - showSurface() dispatcher for named surface navigation

